default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe Bui
defaultlding Regulations model uses the Zero Carbon Homes
default energy profile for different house types to estimate the cost and
default benefits of installing microgeneration 
defaulttechnologies (PV taken as a proxy
default) and energy efficiency measures in new buildings.
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultUsing data from the 2012 consultation and Parsons Brinkerhoff* solar PV costs, the cost to society of the ‘
defaulthalfwaydefault’ approach was estimated at 
default£317mdefault. The analysis also 
defaultestimated that the policy would result in benefits to consumers of 
default£375mdefault. Therefore a cost benefit analysis
default suggest
defaults
default that there would be a net benefit to society of 
default£58mdefault.
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn the latest analysis the benefits to consumers has increased to 
default£391mdefault 
defaultdue to some 
defaultchanges in the dwelling numbers
default and to a small increase in both gas and electricity emission factor. 
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe analysis is based on the Green Book 3.5% SDR. 
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default£311mdefault is the cost of installing PV systems in new buildings using Parsons Brinckerhoff 2012 estimates (in line with DCLG September 2013 IA).
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default£272mdefault would be the cost of installing PVs if Parsons Brinckerhoff 2014 cost estimates were input in the model.
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default£391m defaultis the household savings using DCLG September 2013 revised dwelling assumptions
default.
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTherefore
default default£119m defaultis the net benefit
default default(or 
default£81m defaultusing the 2012 figures)
